          "group": null,
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "API Definition & Versioning Setup"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "Basic API definition:"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "\"proxy\": {"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "  \"listen_path\": \"/trevorblades/\","
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "  \"target_url\": \"https://countries.trevorblades.com\","
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "  \"strip_listen_path\": true"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "}"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "Enable versioning with:"
            },
            {
              "level": 1,
              "text": "use_extended_paths: true"
            },
            {
              "level": 1,
              "text": "not_versioned: true"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "GraphQL to REST middleware lives inside extended_paths.persist_graphql."
            }
          ],
          "text": "API Definition & Versioning Setup\nBasic API definition:\n\"proxy\": {\n  \"listen_path\": \"/trevorblades/\",\n  \"target_url\": \"https://countries.trevorblades.com\",\n  \"strip_listen_path\": true\n}\nEnable versioning with:\nuse_extended_paths: true\nnot_versioned: true\nGraphQL to REST middleware lives inside extended_paths.persist_graphql."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "slide_number": 3,
      "notes": "Once the API definition is in place, versioning plays an important role \u2014 even if you're not managing multiple versions.\nBy setting not_versioned: true and providing a \"Default\" version, you activate the GraphQL-to-REST middleware. This is where the persist_graphql configuration lives.",
