          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "The vital part of this is the extended_paths.persist_graphql field"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "Sample persist_graphql configuration:"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "\"persist_graphql\": ["
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "  {"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "    \"method\": \"GET\","
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "    \"path\": \"/getContinentByCode\","
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "    \"operation\": \"query ($continentCode: ID!) { continent(code: $continentCode) { code name countries { name } } }\","
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "    \"variables\": {"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "      \"continentCode\": \"EU\""
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "    }"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "  }"
            },
            {
              "level": 0,
              "text": "]"
            }
          ],
          "text": "The vital part of this is the extended_paths.persist_graphql field\nSample persist_graphql configuration:\n\"persist_graphql\": [\n  {\n    \"method\": \"GET\",\n    \"path\": \"/getContinentByCode\",\n    \"operation\": \"query ($continentCode: ID!) { continent(code: $continentCode) { code name countries { name } } }\",\n    \"variables\": {\n      \"continentCode\": \"EU\"\n    }\n  }\n]"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "slide_number": 4,
      "notes": "In this final step, we configure the actual persisted query.\nThe path /getContinentByCode becomes a usable REST endpoint.\nWhen Tyk receives a GET request to that path, it will construct and send the defined GraphQL operation to the upstream \u2014 in this case, fetching the continent by code.\nThe query and variables are hardcoded, so it's predictable and easy to cache or control.",
